OL,3,C'Speak out before it's too late,' say
OL,4,Cfamily of woman murdered by boyfriend
OL,6,FA jury at Newcastle Crown Court was
OL,7,Ftold how she suffered 123 bruises and
OL,8,Fcuts, as well as multiple fractures,
OL,9,Fsix cigarette burns which were likely
OL,10,Finflicted as she was dying.
OL,12,FTodd had attacked her over a number of
OL,13,Fdays, and the 36-year-old mother had
OL,14,Falso sustained a brain injury, which
OL,15,Fwould have left her unconscious for
OL,16,F"some days" before she died.
OL,18,F"It's affected a lot of the family,
OL,19,Fthe description of her injuries," Ms
OL,20,FTurnbull told ITV Tyne Tees.
